        <briefdescription>
<para>Set slot value atomically. Three-phase write so lock-free readers never observe a torn {data, linearIdx} pair during a valid-&gt;valid update: (1) flash data to nullptr <ndash/> slot appears &quot;not present&quot; to readers mid-update (2) publish new linearIdx <ndash/> reader still sees INVALID_SLOT (data still null) (3) publish new data <ndash/> commit; slot is now consistently visible Combined with the reader&apos;s nullptr short-circuit, every observable state is internally consistent: pre-update: {old_data, old_idx} mid-update: INVALID_SLOT (brief &quot;not present&quot; window) post-update: {new_data, new_idx} Cost: one extra atomic store on the write path. Reader hot path unchanged. Note: only one writer runs at a time (caller holds the array&apos;s unique write lock), so consecutive <ref refid="structecss_1_1Memory_1_1detail_1_1SparseMap_3_01true_01_4_1af3cede6fe728076c730389c1608f99a7" kindref="member">set()</ref> calls cannot interleave. </para>
        </briefdescription>
